        <dd>
                        <div class="description" id="desc_6456126Comment8541"><div class="xg_user_generated"><p>Hi, Jordan,</p>
<p>Welcome! We've got some forum discussions going on in the different groups (facilitator / host), but, as you noticed, the general outside forum is still a bit empty.</p>
<p>Unfortunately, I don't know how to set up notifications based on events in a certain area. The ning software that we are currently living on isn't the greatest, so we have to be under the constraints of it for now. In general, people follow the local community or the @coderetreat twitter feed. I'm trying to announce new events on the twitter account, and I have some plans for automating it, as well.</p>
<p>There is also an rss feed, although I'm not completely sure how it adds new ones. You can access it via the rss link at the bottom-left of the <a href="../../events" target="_self">events page</a>. Here is a <a href="../../events/event/feed?xn_auth=no" target="_self">direct link</a>.</p></div></div>
