                        <div class="description" id="desc_6456126Comment8713"><div class="xg_user_generated"><p>:) Not on twitter? That's crazy.</p>
<p>This site is hosted on ning, which is very rudimentary for stuff like this.</p>
<p>One option would be to build a small notification feature like you say. People could sign up with a search term, and we could check the rss feed every night. Unfortunately, the rss feed doesn't include a lot of data pulled out into entries, just a big html blob. So, we could search the blob for a match and notify you. This could be a pretty straightforward thing to do on heroku with their scheduler.</p></div></div>
